cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new metric of match and defines single and multiple pattern matching algorithms, which are related to data structures and algorithms.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses indexing and searching for patterns in a text, which are common topics in information retrieval.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper deals with the Cartesian tree, which is a mathematical object.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper presents time complexity analysis for the algorithms.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a possible category as the paper uses the parent-distance representation of the Cartesian tree, which is related to computational geometry.
